## Summary

Adds config-level Policy conformance checks for ingress/channel access posture:

```jsonc
{
  "ingress": {
    "session": {
      "requireDmScope": "per-channel-peer"
    },
    "channels": {
      "allowDmPolicies": ["pairing", "allowlist", "disabled"],
      "denyOpenGroups": true,
      "requireMentionInGroups": true
    }
  }
}
```

This is stacked after #85572 and stays in the config-conformance lane: it observes authored OpenClaw config, emits policy/doctor findings for drift, and does not add runtime enforcement.

The PR also lets `scopes.agents.<scopeName>.ingress` use the scoped-agent container from #85817. Current ingress evidence is default workspace/channel posture, so scoped ingress is intentionally limited to `agentIds` that normalize to `main` until non-default agent ingress evidence exists:

```jsonc
{
  "scopes": {
    "agents": {
      "production-workspace": {
        "agentIds": ["main", "sebastian-prod"],
        "agents": {
          "workspace": { "allowedAccess": ["none", "ro"] }
        }
      },
      "main-ingress": {
        "agentIds": ["main"],
        "ingress": {
          "session": { "requireDmScope": "per-channel-peer" },
          "channels": {
            "allowDmPolicies": ["pairing"],
            "denyOpenGroups": true,
            "requireMentionInGroups": true
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## Verification

- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 docs/cli/policy.md docs/plugins/reference/policy.md docs/plan/policy-agent-scoped-overlays.md extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.ts extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts extensions/policy/src/policy-state.ts`
- `pnpm exec oxlint extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.ts extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts extensions/policy/src/policy-state.ts`
- `pnpm docs:check-mdx docs/cli/policy.md docs/plugins/reference/policy.md docs/plan/policy-agent-scoped-overlays.md`
- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts extensions/policy/src/cli.test.ts -- --reporter=dot`
- `git diff --check`
- `codex review --base sandbox-base`

## Real behavior proof

Behavior addressed: Policy can now express direct-message scope, channel DM policy, open-group denial, group mention-gate, and default scoped-ingress conformance requirements.
Real environment tested: WSL checkout at `/root/src/openclaw-policy-ingress-conformance`.
Exact steps or command run after this patch: Ran focused Policy doctor/CLI tests, Markdown formatting, focused lint, MDX docs validation, whitespace check, signature check, and repeated Codex review against `sandbox-base` until no accepted/actionable findings remained.
Evidence after fix: Policy tests exercise malformed ingress rule shapes, top-level ingress findings, main-scoped ingress findings, disabled channel/account handling, implicit default account handling, wildcard group mention defaults, Telegram multi-account group inheritance, inherited nested group posture, CLI output, and policy-state evidence.
Observed result after fix: 232 focused Vitest tests passed; docs MDX check passed; formatting/lint/whitespace checks passed; final Codex review reported no actionable correctness issues. Latest signed commit is `0de005d88da638ec0f51f54533f34b4fe6f3ced8`.
What was not tested: Live channel runtimes were not launched because this PR intentionally checks config conformance only, not runtime message delivery or enforcement.

